rComments: Lectures are very content heavy. Little practice problems are given by him to help prepare for midterms and exams.
Honestly, doesn't deserve to teach. Specifically, he doesn't deserve to teach because he doesn't really teach. Too many times he would say "you can figure this out yourself".

His notes are unclear (useless). I didn't understand a thing in his classes. The worst prof I've had in 3 years of undergrad.
Very very helpful prof - he is very good if you drop by his office and ask questions, a nice merry man

He taught Process Engineering in the chem eng department. I learned a lot from just going to his lectures. His notes may be messy, but they contain all the details that you need to solve a problem. The tutorial problems are hard, but you can manage if you ask questions. He is really fair when it comes to tests, but they can still be hard
